# Copy this file to ".env" and paste your real keys after the "=".
# Never commit the real .env — it is git-ignored for you.
#
# Sage's DEFAULT search sources (DuckDuckGo, Wikipedia, GDELT) need NO keys at all.
# Sage's DEFAULT brain (Claude on your Claude Code subscription) needs NO key either —
# so the out-of-the-box setup needs NOTHING in this file.

# --- LLM brain ---------------------------------------------------------------
# DEFAULT (SAGE_LLM unset) = Claude on your Claude Code SUBSCRIPTION via the Agent
# SDK. No key required. Do NOT set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY — it is NOT needed for the
# default, and if set it makes the SDK bill the pay-per-token API instead of your
# subscription (llm.py warns you if it sees it).
#
# Switch brains with the SAGE_LLM env var (one switch, see llm.py):
#
#   SAGE_LLM=gemini    -> needs GEMINI_API_KEY below
#   SAGE_LLM=deepseek  -> needs DEEPSEEK_API_KEY below

# Google Gemini (free) — only for SAGE_LLM=gemini.
# Free key: https://aistudio.google.com -> "Get API key".
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-free-gemini-api-key-here

# DeepSeek — only for SAGE_LLM=deepseek.
# Key: https://platform.deepseek.com -> API keys.
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=your-deepseek-api-key-here

# --- Optional search upgrades (higher-quality web search; behind the seam) ----
# Set WEB_BACKEND in search.py to "tavily" or "brave" to use these.
# TAVILY_API_KEY=your-tavily-free-tier-key
# BRAVE_API_KEY=your-brave-free-tier-key
